<plot>"Faux," is a contemporary tale about a woman who deals courageously and creatively with heartbreak. Sweetly seductive Tweety, curator at a local gallery, has her belief in love tested when she is forced to discover how far she will go to believe what she wants to believe. Tweety and her boyfriend JR have been together 5 good years...but when she is unable to reach him at a time he should be reachable, Tweety surreptitiously checks J.R.'s voice mail and discovers an "I love you message," from another woman. Tweety then begins to question the entire relationship and wonder what was true in their five years together.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?191195</url></doc>
